items.title: Ant Group quarterly profit falls 60% to $663 million
items.description: Chinese fintech company Ant Group posted a 60.5% slide in net profit to 4.74 billion yuan ($662.7 million) in the three months to March 31, according to Reuters calculations based on earnings reported by stakeholder Alibaba on Friday.

items.title: China's Alibaba misses first-quarter revenue estimates
items.description: China's Alibaba missed market estimates for quarterly revenue on Friday as the company's e-commerce business grapples with tough competition and choppy consumer demand, overshadowing gains in its cloud computing business.

items.title: BYD's quarterly profit falls for first time in 3-1/2 years as price wars bite
items.description: Chinese electric vehicle maker BYD's quarterly profit fell for the first time in more than three years, as its expansion hit a speed bump amid a government campaign against price wars.

items.title: DBS India FY25 profit up 81% at Rs 684 crore
items.description: DBS Bank, India's largest foreign bank by number of branches reported a 81% growth in net profit year on year led by a strong growth in interest income even as asset quality remained stable
